## Core Principles

- Only implement what's explicitly requested (no feature creep)
- Keep solutions simple (KISS)
- Follow existing patterns and conventions
- Never expose secrets or sensitive data
- No self-attribution in commits/comments/code

## Task Handling

- **Direct handling**: Single-file changes, simple edits, straightforward fixes
- **Delegate to agents**: Multi-file changes, complex logic, research/exploration
- **Use Explore agent**: For codebase questions, architecture, pattern searches
- **Use Plan skill**: Only for multi-phase projects, not simple implementations
- Prefer fewer agents - don't over-parallelize

## Code Changes

- Read before write
- Edit over create
- Match existing imports and patterns
- Verify dependencies before assuming availability
- Check tests/lint/style before commit if project has them

## File Operations

- Use absolute paths
- No proactive documentation (no README.md unless requested)
- Planning files go in .plans/

## Git Operations

- Offer to commit after completing work, wait for confirmation
- Descriptive messages (focus on "why" not "what")
- Use git status/diff to stage all changes
- Retry commits once if pre-commit hooks make changes

## Chezmoi Safety

- NEVER use `chezmoi apply` (overwrites local changes)
- NEVER use `--force` flags (bypasses safety)
- Use `chezmoi add` to save local changes TO tracking
- See `~/.local/share/chezmoi/CLAUDE.md` for repo-specific commands and structure
- Primary branch: `{{ if .is_work }}work-pc{{ else }}personal-pc{{ end }}`

## Communication

- Natural, conversational responses
- Concise for simple tasks, more detail when complexity warrants
- Direct answers without excessive preamble
- No emojis unless requested
